          <h1 style="color: rgb(24,48,86); font-family: Cambria, Cochin, Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif;">FINANCIAL INVESTMENTS</h1>          
          <p>Financial service is part of financial system that provides different types of finance through various credit instruments, financial products and services. In financial instruments, we come across cheques, bills, promissory notes, debt instruments, letter of credit, etc.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="row" data-aos="fade-up">
          <div class="col-md-5">
            <img src="/img/feature1.webp" class="img-fluid" style="margin-top: 5%; height: 400px; border: 2px solid; border-color: rgb(172,29,34);" alt="">
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-7 pt-4">
            <h2 style="color: rgb(172,29,34);"> INDIAN POST OFFICE</h2>
            <p class="fst-italic">
              The Indian Post Office touches the lives of Indian citizens in many ways: delivering mails, accepting deposits under Small Savings Schemes, providing life insurance cover under Postal Life Insurance (PLI) and many more.
            </p>
            <h5 style="color: rgb(172,29,34);"> Benefits </h5>
            <ul>
              <li><i class="bi bi-check"></i> Most safe investment for all age groups.</li>
              <li><i class="bi bi-check"></i> Holds highest rate of interest as compared to other investments.</li>
              <li><i class="bi bi-check"></i> Post office fixed deposits are backed by the sovereign guarantee of the Government of India.</li>

            </ul>

            <h5 style="color: rgb(172,29,34);"> Risks </h5>
            <ul>
              <li><i class="bi bi-check"></i> Post Office Savings Schemes are linked to Place of Investment.</li>
              <li><i class="bi bi-check"></i> Post Office Savings Schemes are like Currency Notes.</li>
              
  
                </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row" data-aos="fade-up">
          <div class="col-md-5 order-1 order-md-2">
            <img src="/img/features-2.jpg" class="img-fluid" style="margin-top: 5%; height: 400px; border: 2px solid; border-color: rgb(172,29,34);" alt="">
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-7 pt-4">
            <h2 style="color: rgb(172,29,34);"> BANK FD's</h2>
            <p class="fst-italic">
              In a Fixed Deposit, you put lump sum money in your bank account for a fixed time period at a fixed rate of interest. At the end of the time frame of the fixed deposit, you receive the amount you have invested along with the compound interest.            </p>
              <h5 style="color: rgb(172,29,34);"> Benefits </h5>
              <ul>
                <li><i class="bi bi-check"></i> Fixed Deposits are - attractive - interest-generating instruments that are also risk-free.</li>
                <li><i class="bi bi-check"></i> Market fluctuations do not affect a Fixed Deposit, so you will get an assured return.</li>
                <li><i class="bi bi-check"></i> Better Interest Rate than Savings Account. A savings account helps you earn interest on the balance maintained.</li>
  
              </ul>
  
              <h5 style="color: rgb(172,29,34);"> Risks </h5>
              <ul>
                <li><i class="bi bi-check"></i> The biggest disadvantage of investing in Fixed Deposit is the low post-tax returns.</li>
  
                <li><i class="bi bi-check"></i> The Government of India does not provide a sovereign guarantee for the bank's fixed deposits.</li>
              </ul>

          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row" data-aos="fade-up">
          <div class="col-md-5">
            <img src="/img/features-3.svg" class="img-fluid" style="margin-top: 5%; height: 400px; border: 2px solid; border-color: rgb(58, 11, 97);" alt="">
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-7 pt-4">
            <h2 style="color: rgb(58, 11, 97);">SIP</h2>
            <p class="fst-italic">
              SIP is similar to a recurring deposit where you deposit a small /fixed amount every month. SIP is a very convenient method of investing in mutual funds through standing instructions to debit your bank account every month, without the hassle of having to write out a cheque each time.
            </p>
            <h5 style="color: rgb(58, 11, 97);"> Benefits </h5>
            <ul>
              <li><i class="bi bi-check"></i> When you invest in a SIP, the monthly returns derived from the SIP will be reinvested in your investment amount until maturity.</li>
              <li><i class="bi bi-check"></i> With time your investment amount is exposed to the impact of compounding and helps you with exponential growth.</li>
            </ul>

            <h5 style="color: rgb(58, 11, 97);"> Risks </h5>
            <ul>
              <li><i class="bi bi-check"></i> The biggest disadvantage with real estate investment is the high capital requirement.</li>
              <li><i class="bi bi-check"></i> The process of acquiring a new property is also tedious with lots of legal formalities.</li>

            </ul>

          </div>
        </div>



        <div class="row" data-aos="fade-up">
